@startuml VibeCodium - State Diagram (Project)
title VibeCodium - Ciclul de Viață Proiect

[*] --> Created : User creates project

Created --> Editing : Open in editor

Editing --> Editing : Edit files
Editing --> Running : Click "Run"
Editing --> Collaborating : Share session
Editing --> Snapshotted : Save checkpoint
Editing --> Deploying : Click "Deploy"
Editing --> Archived : User archives
Editing --> Deleted : User deletes

Running --> Editing : View results
Running --> Failed : Execution error

Failed --> Editing : Fix errors

Collaborating --> Editing : All users disconnect
Collaborating --> Collaborating : Multiple users edit

Snapshotted --> Editing : Continue editing
Snapshotted --> Restored : Restore checkpoint

Restored --> Editing : Resume work

Deploying --> Deployed : Vercel success
Deploying --> DeployFailed : Vercel error

Deployed --> Editing : Make changes
DeployFailed --> Editing : Fix issues

Archived --> Editing : User unarchives

Deleted --> [*]

@enduml


@startuml VibeCodium - State Diagram (Collaboration Session)
title VibeCodium - Sesiune Colaborare

[*] --> Idle : No users connected

Idle --> SingleUser : First user joins

SingleUser --> Syncing : Load Y.Doc state
Syncing --> Active : Sync complete

Active --> SingleUser : User editing
Active --> MultiUser : Second user joins

MultiUser --> Syncing : New user sync
Syncing --> MultiUser : Sync complete
MultiUser --> MultiUser : Concurrent edits
MultiUser --> Conflict : Simultaneous edits
Conflict --> MultiUser : CRDT merge

MultiUser --> SingleUser : Users disconnect
SingleUser --> Idle : Last user disconnects

Active --> Expired : Session timeout
MultiUser --> Expired : Session timeout
Expired --> [*]

@enduml


@startuml VibeCodium - Sequence (Real-Time Collaboration)
title VibeCodium - Colaborare Real-Time

participant "User 1\nBrowser" as U1
participant "User 2\nBrowser" as U2
participant "WebSocket\nServer" as WS
participant "Yjs\nY.Doc" as Yjs
participant "SQLite\nDB" as DB

U1 -> WS : Connect ws://server/ws/collab/proj_123
WS -> Yjs : Get or create Y.Doc
WS -> U1 : Send sync-step-1 (state vector)
U1 -> WS : Send sync-step-2 (missing updates)
WS -> U1 : Send sync-step-2 (server updates)
note over U1,WS : User 1 fully synced

U2 -> WS : Connect ws://server/ws/collab/proj_123
WS -> U2 : Send sync-step-1
U2 -> WS : Send sync-step-2
WS -> U2 : Send sync-step-2
note over U2,WS : User 2 fully synced

U1 -> U1 : Type "hello" in editor
U1 -> WS : Send Yjs update (insert "hello")
WS -> Yjs : Apply update
WS -> U2 : Broadcast update
U2 -> U2 : Apply update to Monaco
note over U2 : Sees "hello" appear

U2 -> U2 : Type "world" after "hello"
U2 -> WS : Send Yjs update (insert " world")
WS -> Yjs : Apply update
WS -> U1 : Broadcast update
U1 -> U1 : Apply update to Monaco
note over U1 : Sees "hello world"

U1 -> U1 : Click "Save"
U1 -> WS : HTTP POST /api/projects/.../files/index.js
WS -> DB : UPDATE files SET content = "hello world"
DB --> WS : OK
WS --> U1 : 200 OK

@enduml


@startuml VibeCodium - Sequence (AI Agent Loop)
title VibeCodium - AI Agent Loop

actor User
participant "VibeChat" as Client
participant "AgentRoute" as Server
participant "DeepSeek\nAPI" as LLM
participant "Tool\nExecutor" as Tools
participant "File\nSystem" as FS

User -> Client : Type "read main.py and add error handling"
Client -> Server : POST /api/agent/chat (SSE stream)

Server -> LLM : POST /v1/chat/completions (stream=true)
note over Server,LLM : Messages: system prompt + history + user message

LLM --> Server : SSE: {"delta": {"content": "I'll"}}
Server --> Client : SSE: {"token": "I'll"}
LLM --> Server : SSE: {"delta": {"content": " read"}}
Server --> Client : SSE: {"token": " read"}
LLM --> Server : SSE: {"delta": {"content": " the file"}}
Server --> Client : SSE: {"token": " the file"}

LLM --> Server : SSE: {"delta": {"tool_calls": [...]}}
note over Server : Tool: read_file(main.py)
Server -> Tools : executeTools(read_file, {path: "main.py"})
Tools -> FS : Read main.py
FS --> Tools : content: "def main():\n  print('hi')"
Tools --> Server : {result: "def main()..."}

Server -> LLM : POST /v1/chat/completions (add tool result)
note over Server,LLM : Messages: [..., tool result]

LLM --> Server : SSE: {"delta": {"content": "Here's the improved code"}}
Server --> Client : SSE: {"token": "Here's the improved code"}

LLM --> Server : SSE: {"delta": {"tool_calls": [write_file, ...]}}
note over Server : Tool: write_file(main.py)
Server -> Tools : executeTools(write_file, {...})
Tools -> FS : Write main.py
FS --> Tools : OK
Tools --> Server : {result: "File written successfully"}

Server -> LLM : POST /v1/chat/completions (add tool result)
LLM --> Server : SSE: {"delta": {"content": "Done!"}}
Server --> Client : SSE: {"token": "Done!"}
LLM --> Server : SSE: [DONE]
Server --> Client : SSE: event: done

Client -> User : Display full message

@enduml


@startuml VibeCodium - Sequence (Docker Execution)
title VibeCodium - Execuție Cod în Docker

actor User
participant Client
participant "Execution\nRoute" as Server
participant Docker
participant Container

User -> Client : Click "Run"
Client -> Server : POST /api/execute\n{projectId, language, entrypoint}

Server -> Server : Get project files from SQLite
Server -> Server : Create temp dir /tmp/exec_xyz
Server -> Server : Write all files to temp dir

Server -> Docker : docker run --rm -v /tmp/exec_xyz:/code\n--network none --memory 512m\npython:3.11 python /code/main.py

Docker -> Container : Spawn container
Container -> Container : Execute python /code/main.py
note over Container : Running user code...

alt Success
  Container --> Docker : stdout: "Hello World"\nexitCode: 0
  Docker --> Server : {stdout, stderr, exitCode}
  Server -> Server : Cleanup temp dir
  Server --> Client : {stdout: "Hello World", stderr: "", exitCode: 0}
  Client -> User : Display output
else Error
  Container --> Docker : stderr: "SyntaxError"\nexitCode: 1
  Docker --> Server : {stdout, stderr, exitCode}
  Server -> Server : Cleanup temp dir
  Server --> Client : {stdout: "", stderr: "SyntaxError", exitCode: 1}
  Client -> User : Display error
else Timeout
  note over Container : 30s timeout exceeded
  Docker -> Container : SIGKILL
  Docker --> Server : {stderr: "Timeout", exitCode: 137}
  Server -> Server : Cleanup temp dir
  Server --> Client : {stderr: "Execution timeout"}
  Client -> User : Display timeout error
end

@enduml


@startuml VibeCodium - Sequence (Vercel Deploy)
title VibeCodium - Deploy pe Vercel

actor User
participant Client
participant "Deploy\nRoute" as Server
participant "GitHub\nAPI" as GitHub
participant "Vercel\nAPI" as Vercel

User -> Client : Click "Deploy"
Client -> Server : POST /api/deploy {projectId}

Server -> Server : Check user has vercelToken & githubToken

alt No tokens
  Server --> Client : 400 Bad Request: "Missing tokens"
  Client -> User : Redirect to /profile
  User -> Client : Add tokens
  Client -> Server : POST /api/deploy {projectId}
end

Server -> GitHub : POST /user/repos\n{name: "vibecodium-proj_123", private: true}
GitHub --> Server : {clone_url: "https://github.com/user/..."}

Server -> Server : Create temp dir
Server -> Server : Write project files
Server -> Server : git init && add && commit
Server -> Server : git push origin main
GitHub --> Server : Push accepted

Server -> Vercel : POST /v13/deployments\n{name: "...", gitSource: {...}}
Vercel --> Server : {id: "dpl_xyz", readyState: "BUILDING"}

Server -> Server : Poll deployment status every 5s
loop Until ready or timeout
  Server -> Vercel : GET /v13/deployments/dpl_xyz
  Vercel --> Server : {readyState: "BUILDING"}
  Server -> Server : Wait 5s
end

Vercel --> Server : {readyState: "READY",\nurl: "vibecodium-proj-123.vercel.app"}
Server -> Server : Save DeployedApp to MongoDB
Server --> Client : {url: "...", status: "ready"}
Client -> User : Open deployment in new tab

@enduml


